videos.headline: West with early lead in WNBA All-Star game
videos.description: Maya Moore and Diana Taurasi rain 3-pointers to help the West get out to an early lead in the WNBA All-Star Game.

videos.headline: Quigley wins WNBA 3-point contest
videos.description: Allie Quigley of the Chicago Sky wins the 3-point contest with a final round of 27.

videos.headline: Clarendon beats the buzzer
videos.description: Layshia Clarendon of the Atlanta Dream converts a tip-in as time expires at the end of the third quarter.

videos.headline: Jones throws down
videos.description: Jonquel Jones of the Connecticut Sun end the WNBA All-Star Game with a dunk as the West beats the East 130-121.

videos.headline: Moore named All-Star Game MVP
videos.description: Minnesota Lynx's Maya Moore wins her second WNBA All-Star Game MVP, scoring a game-high 23 points.
